---
description: Auth and financial data handling — load for anything touching login, roles, or payments
alwaysApply: false
---
- Passwords: bcrypt/argon2 hashed, never stored or logged in plaintext.
- JWT or session-based auth — either is fine, but be consistent, and store
  role in the token/session, re-verify role server-side on every request.
- Payment gateway is Cashfree. Never trust client-side "payment success" callbacks
  alone — an invoice is only marked paid after Cashfree's webhook confirms it
  server-side, with signature verification on every webhook payload.
- Cashfree credentials (client id / client secret) live in server-side env vars
  only — never in client/ code, never committed to git.
- Webhook handler must be idempotent (Cashfree can retry/resend the same
  event) — check payment/order id before applying an update twice.
- Never expose other residents' contact/vehicle details across flats unless
  the requester is manager/admin/staff.
